10985.title: Avatar: The Last Airbender
10985.description: Second part to "The Day of Black Sun, Part 1: The Invasion". The eclipse has started and the gang only has a few minutes to get into an underground bunker and find and defeat Ozai. Zuko confront his father and learn about his mother's banishment while Aang, Sokka and Toph fight Azula and her Dai Li agents.

10986.title: Avatar: The Last Airbender
10986.description: The gang leaves the Fire Nation, humbled and embarrassed by the failure of the invasion. They head to the Western Air Temple. However, unknown to them, Zuko is also following them in the hope of joining their group to teach Aang firebending.

10987.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
10987.description: When his pet amoeba Spot has puppies, Plankton decides to use them in another of his nefarious plots. // Mr. Krabs is too scared to get his physical, but if he doesn't pass, the Krusty Krab will be shut down!

10988.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
10988.description: Plankton poses as a wish-granting genie in his latest scheme to get the secret formula. // Mr. Krabs' new Krabby soup is a hit - until some heat-loving hippies move into the soup vat!

10989.title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles
10989.description: Leo goes behind Splinter's back when he stages a rescue for Karai, whose desire for revenge against Shredder brings about grave consequences for them all.

10990.title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles
10990.description: As Donnie becomes increasingly jealous of April and Casey's relationship, April is kidnapped by an evil spirit who intends to drain April's powers.

10991.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
10991.description: Po saves a girl from some bandits, only to learn that she's engaged to be married to the Dragon Warrior.

10992.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
10992.description: During a fight with Tong Fo, Po is struck by lightning, giving him the power to read minds.

10993.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
10993.description: Private discovers a stack of lost comic books. Skipper immediately commands their destruction, citing their risky influence. // Shakespeare in the park has inspired Private as he struts around the zoo spouting iambic pentameter laden insults.

10994.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
10994.description: The penguins have had enough of the crazy lemurs 24 hour parting! They hack into the zoo habitat schematic and successfully transfer the lemurs to the petting zoo. // The penguins journey to the bottom of the Atlantic for 100 year-old preserved herring.

10995.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
10995.description: Squidward is so tired that SpongeBob & Patrick can't wake him up, but they won't let him miss his big audition! // Mr. Krabs & his crew cater a fancy party, but they might be out of their depth with their new wealthy customers.

10996.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
10996.description: When SpongeBob cooks at home, Mr. Krabs' customers leave his restaurant and head for SpongeBob's Place. // When Plankton gets kicked out of the house, it's up to SpongeBob to teach him how to win his computer wife back.

10997.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
10997.description: After a misunderstanding, SpongeBob and Patrick try to prove their life insurance protects them from any danger! // When SpongeBob blows himself a bubble boat, everyone in town wants one! Everyone except Mrs. Puff, that is.

10998.title: Nella The Princess Knight
10998.description: Nella searches for a magical crystal to make it snow for their annual 'Snow Festival'. // Nella and her friends must play as a team to win the Castlehaven gobletball tournament.

10999.title: Nella The Princess Knight
10999.description: While camping with the Knight Trekkers, Blaine goes to extreme lengths to earn his first badge. // Nella finally brings two arguing groups of dragons together, but Trinket accidentally reignites their rivalry.

11000.title: Bubble Guppies
11000.description: It's going to be the best doghouse EVER! But before Bubble Puppy can move into his new doggy digs, the Bubble Guppies have to build it. Help them build it while discovering all about construction.

11001.title: Bubble Guppies
11001.description: At the Bubble Guppies' restaurant, the group is waiting tables, cooking food,and preparing to serve their most difficult customer yet. But is there anything on the menu that can get the Grumpfish grinning?

11002.title: Dora the Explorer
11002.description: Dora and Boots go on an underwater adventure that takes them all the way to the bottom of the ocean.

11003.title: Dora the Explorer
11003.description: Dora and Boots are getting ready to make a wish on the first star in the sky when the star falls! It's up to Dora and Boots to bring Little Star back home to the Moon.

11004.title: Rusty Rivets
11004.description: When Ranger Anna crash lands her planes in the distant savannah, Rusty and Ruby realize they need a new vehicle that can not only travel the distance, but aid them in their builds. Thus, the Mobile Rivet Lab is born!

11005.title: Rusty Rivets
11005.description: When Ranger Anna gets stuck in a tree while observing monkeys, Rusty and Ruby make a monkey of their own to save her... Botarilla! // Ranger Anna and Liam get trapped in the ranger station by a giant snowball!

11006.title: Blaze And The Monster Machines
11006.description: Blaze and his driver AJ are introduced to a world of racing Monster Machines. But when a truck named Crusher uses tricks to try and win the Championship Race, Blaze will do everything he can to help his friends and beat Crusher to the finish line.

11007.title: Blaze And The Monster Machines
11007.description: Blaze and his driver AJ are introduced to a world of racing Monster Machines. But when a truck named Crusher uses dirty tricks to try and win the Championship Race, Blaze will do everything he can to help his friends and beat Crusher to the finish line.

11008.title: PAW Patrol
11008.description: It’s Adventure Bay Western Days. The whole town is enjoying the activities when a herd of cows escape from a train at the railway station. Now it’s like the real old west, with the PAW Patrol rounding up cows. Yeehaw!/When their friend Alex decides he wants to be a member of the PAW Patrol the PUPS and Ryder let him come along for the ride. Rescuing Cali the cat from farmer Yumi’s barn becomes more of a challenge when Alex tries to help!

11009.title: PAW Patrol
11009.description: Alex loses his back pack on the first day of school! Ryder and the Paw Patrol need to help him find it before the school bus comes./It’s Chase’s birthday and the pups are planning a surprise party. A storm causes the power to go out. The Paw Patrol have to fix the power and save Chases Birthday party.

11010.title: PAW Patrol
11010.description: It’s a hot day and the pups head for the water park – but the pool is empty! Paw Patrol to the rescue. Digger and Rocky step in and help Ryder get water to the pool. Pool Day is back on!/When the animals don’t show up in time for the Circus to start; Ryder and the Paw Patrol step in to help.

11011.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
11011.description: Mr. Krabs tries to make even more money by turning a hole in the Krusty Krab wall into a cash-making drive-thru window! // Tony Fast Jr., the son of a famous race car driver, tries to teach SpongeBob how to drive.

11012.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
11012.description: Everyone in Bikini Bottom is competing in a worm-sled race to the South Pole. Will SpongeBob and the gang make it to the frosty finish line to claim the big prize…one million clams!

11013.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
11013.description: When Patrick suddenly grows a very grown-up beard, he decides it’s time to act like a grown-up and perhaps Squiward is the perfect squid to help him! // While preparing to give an oral report for boating school, SpongeBob comes down with a horrible case of stage fright.

11014.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
11014.description: Kowalski’s obsession with Doris the dolphin drives him to invent a love ray, the Love-U-Laser. It works like a charm until Alice falls for a trashcan, Julien falls for Mort, and Skipper orders the ray to be put in reverse. Private gets hit by the reverse ray and instantly loathes Kowalski. Matters get much worse as the loathe ray explodes and everybody hates Kowalski! He’s only got one shot to stop being the most loathed penguin in the world. // Told as a courtroom flashback, Kowalski unwisely revives Jiggles in a small, whipped cream-eating version. The little green cubes multiply on impact, however, and are soon threatening to cover the surface of the earth. As the Jiggli multiply out of control, will the team be able to prevent the jiggli-fication of the world?

11015.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
11015.description: The Commissioner flips his lid, literally. His toupee blows off and sticks to Maurice, who also gets red cheeks and a skinned tail, all by accident. Julien and Mort chase him with sticks, intent on beating the “monster” stuck to Maurice’s head. The baboon ladies take Maurice in, protecting and pampering him because they mistakenly think he’s a male baboon. It’s up to the penguins to get the toupee back and restore it to its rightful scalp. // Shelly the ostrich gets stuck in drying cement and only Rico can save her. Shelly falls for him hard as a result, however, Rico’s heart forever belongs to his doll. Shelly swipes the doll and tries hard to win his heart, but Rico doesn’t budge and his doll is accidently hauled off in a recycle truck. The penguins give chase but are left hopelessly in the dust. Shelly, wanting to make amends, tosses them on her back and sprints after the truck – can she possibly catch it?

11016.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
11016.description: Po and Tigress must track down and stop a messenger from delivering a scroll that could thrust China into all-out war!

11017.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
11017.description: Po and the Furious Five meet their greatest challenge yet: a supernatural creature who is invincible to the powers of kung fu.

11018.title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles
11018.description: Raph's hot-headed impulsiveness lands him in deep trouble when he accidentally damages a machine that forces him to switch minds with a Kraang.

11019.title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles
11019.description: Leo goes behind Splinter's back when he stages a rescue for Karai, whose desire for revenge against Shredder brings about grave consequences for them all.

11020.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
11020.description: Determined to uncover Plankton’s next devious plot, Mr. Krabs sends SpongeBob and Patrick to spy on him. // Watch an instructional video on boating techniques with Squidward and SpongeBob. // Mr. Krabs holds a contest for his employees: The first one to learn the names of every Krusty Krab customer wins a tropical vacation.

11021.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
11021.description: After arriving one minute late for work, SpongeBob decides to move into the Krusty Krab so that he will never be late to work again. // When Plankton secretly turns down the thermostat at the Krusty Krab the entire restaurant freezes over. But with a couple of frozen Krabby Patties tied to his shoes for skates, SpongeBob turns the frozen floor into an ice rink

11022.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
11022.description: The scariest roller coaster ever has just opened at Bikini Bottom's amusement park. At first SpongeBob and Patrick are determined to ride it, but the more they think about how scary it is the more they chicken out. // Plankton tricks SpongeBob, Patrick and Squidward into fixing up the Chum Bucket.

11023.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
11023.description: Thanks to Po, Hundun opens up his own noodle shop in the village, threatening to put Mr. Ping out of business.

11024.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
11024.description: Over Po's objections, Shifu calls in a noble Samurai prawn to help take down a villain from Japan.

11025.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
11025.description: When Kowalski's ray designed to freshen spoiled food accidentally hits Skipper before falling down a storm drain, the leader is turned into a baby penguin, albeit retaining much of Skipper's adult personality. // After learning of Savio's escape from Hoboken on a TV news report, the penguins organize an effort to protect the zoo from the vengeful boa.

11026.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
11026.description: Kowalski’s obsession with Doris the dolphin drives him to invent a love ray, the Love-U-Laser. It works like a charm until Alice falls for a trashcan, Julien falls for Mort, and Skipper orders the ray to be put in reverse. Private gets hit by the reverse ray and instantly loathes Kowalski. Matters get much worse as the loathe ray explodes and everybody hates Kowalski! He’s only got one shot to stop being the most loathed penguin in the world. // Told as a courtroom flashback, Kowalski unwisely revives Jiggles in a small, whipped cream-eating version. The little green cubes multiply on impact, however, and are soon threatening to cover the surface of the earth. As the Jiggli multiply out of control, will the team be able to prevent the jiggli-fication of the world?

11027.title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles
11027.description: At home, Mikey always messes things up, but when the Turtles go to the bizarre realm of Dimension X, he's the only one who can figure the place out.

11028.title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles
11028.description: Leo and Donnie disagree about their plan to stop the Kraang invasion. When Leo makes a critical mistake, he is separated from the team and Donnie must step up as a leader.

11029.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
11029.description: SpongeBob loves Krabby Patties so much, he just can't help singing and dancing when he's around the delicious sandwiches. // When Stanley, SpongeBob's klutzy, absent-minded cousin, comes to visit Bikini Bottom, he quickly turns SpongeBob's life upside down.

11030.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
11030.description: When Squidward sees Squilliam on a TV show about fancy homes, Squidward becomes infuriated and tries to outdo him. // When SpongeBob mistakenly thinks that Plankton is starting a band, Plankton decides to use this to his advantage.

11031.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
11031.description: When Mr. Krabs sees SpongeBob pick something up off the street, he begins to obsess over the idea that SpongeBob found a penny - a penny that he should have found first! // SpongeBob's boating school class is going on a field trip.

11032.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
11032.description: Shifu suggests Po takes a vow of silence to help him focus, but his plan goes awry when the panda starts an armed conflict by keeping his mouth shut.

11033.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
11033.description: Once deemed a hero, cobra Fu-xi has turned renegade and is attacking the Valley of Peace. When the villagers adopt an anti-snake sentiment, will Viper help stop Fu-xi...or join him?

11034.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
11034.description: The Commissioner flips his lid, literally. His toupee blows off and sticks to Maurice, who also gets red cheeks and a skinned tail, all by accident. Julien and Mort chase him with sticks, intent on beating the “monster” stuck to Maurice’s head. The baboon ladies take Maurice in, protecting and pampering him because they mistakenly think he’s a male baboon. It’s up to the penguins to get the toupee back and restore it to its rightful scalp. // Shelly the ostrich gets stuck in drying cement and only Rico can save her. Shelly falls for him hard as a result, however, Rico’s heart forever belongs to his doll. Shelly swipes the doll and tries hard to win his heart, but Rico doesn’t budge and his doll is accidently hauled off in a recycle truck. The penguins give chase but are left hopelessly in the dust. Shelly, wanting to make amends, tosses them on her back and sprints after the truck – can she possibly catch it?

11035.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
11035.description: The penguin’s worst nightmare has come true. After a sailing trip gone wrong they wind up in the Hoboken Zoo. Strangely, the animals are happy, the zoo is a paradise, and life couldn’t be better! Zookeeper Frances takes outstanding care of all of them – or does she? Something sinister bubbles under the surface – the happy animals are actually androids, and the real animals are held captive in a dungeon. They’re too messy and Zookeeper Frances can’t stand a mess! A rescue comes from a very unlikely source, and the final battle could go either way!

11036.title: Avatar: The Last Airbender
11036.description: Aang is ready to start his firebending training. However, as Zuko attempts to teach him, he realizes he has lost all his firebending power; as he is no longer drawing his firebending power from rage, anger and his desire to capture Aang. They journey to find the true source of firebending.

11037.title: Avatar: The Last Airbender
11037.description: Sokka and Zuko break into The Boiling Rock Prison, the Fire Nation's highest security prison, to rescue Hakoda. When they develope an escape plan after finding Hakoda not there, other prisoners get involved and ruin it. Now the two, and a recently discovered Suki have to find another way out of the inescapable fortress.

11038.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
11038.description: Plankton has demolished the Chum Bucket! In its place, he has built a Roman coliseum. // The Bikini Bottom Symphony is accepting submissions for their composition contest, and Squidward is determined to win.

11039.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
11039.description: When Squidward points out to SpongeBob that he's not normal, SpongeBob makes it his mission to become normal. // SpongeBob wakes up one morning to find that everyone in Bikini Bottom is gone - even Gary!

11040.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
11040.description: While working at the Krusty Krab, SpongeBob accidentally gets a splinter. // SpongeBob and Patrick are having fun with their new slide whistles, and, of course, it's driving Squidward crazy.

11041.title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles
11041.description: Leo and Donnie disagree about their plan to stop the Kraang invasion. When Leo makes a critical mistake, he is separated from the team and Donnie must step up as a leader.

11042.title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles
11042.description: The team comes to grips with the possibility that Leo won't get better, while things only get worse: a new mutant captures Raph!

11043.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
11043.description: The local thugs love Mr. Ping's soup so much, the noodle shop becomes a villain hangout...with Mr. Ping as their unknowing crime boss!

11044.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
11044.description: Po befriends a group of young (and adorable) orphans-who also happen to be stealing money and goods from the villagers. Will Po be able to reform the kids or fall into the clutches of their evil leader?

11045.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
11045.description: The notorious Vesuvius Twins have adopted Skipper and King Julien and brought the animal’s home to their luxury apartment. Not to spoil and pamper - but to fight each other over shiny baubles! The rest of the penguins and lemurs attempt a rescue but are captured themselves and made to perform in a painful “circus” the twins put together. The tables are going to need to be turned to get this circus out of town. // Kowalski has another breakthrough invention, tiny robots that group together and not only fix broken tools and appliances, but run them as well. The penguins can just sit back and let the “Nanites” take care of all their chores! The problem is, the Nanites are programmed to protect the penguins at all costs, and ultimately seal the birds inside their lair. The only way to escape is to do battle with a giant, nasty, Nanite robot.

11046.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
11046.description: Private has an arch enemy in the form of Dale the snail. Why does this snail hate Private so much? It's because Private allegedly smashed the little guy, and keeps smashing him albeit accidentally. Even a public apology ends with Dale getting crushed. Sadly, Dale should never have been enemies with Private to begin with - it was a different penguin who did him wrong. // King Julien becomes enamored of a giant toilet the penguins have built. He wants to use it as his new throne, only the toilet is actually a stink bomb the penguins built to trap Dr. Blowhole. Julien accidently gets trapped, bound tightly to the bomb, so the penguins must try to stop it from detonating, all while going on a wild truck chase through New York. They end up in a New Jersey dump, and Skipper must show a sensitive side before all is lost.

11047.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
11047.description: Marlene plans a game night to help the zoo animals bond but it takes a terrible turn when the snacks run out. While Kowalski, Maurice, and Mort go on a snack run the gaming animals begin to fight over the games - cheating, sore losing, unwilling participation… chaos! The snack runners get trapped by the law at the store, and the zoo animals have to reconcile quickly in order to pull off a risky rescue. This isn’t the kind of bonding Marlene had in mind! // Elmer the dog wants a friend, and thinks he found one in Mort. The penguins are compelled to rescue him, but Elmer doesn’t want to give the little lemur up! Max the cat is recruited to help, and Max uses his dog expertise to lead the boys to the giant dog. Mort is rescued, but at what cost? The penguins think Max has met his slobbery doom in the jaws of the giant mastiff.

11048.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
11048.description: Everyone is in awe of Larry the Lobster's daredevil ways, especially SpongeBob and Patrick. // Everybody who's anybody is going to a big party in Bikini Bottom, but you have to be a certain shade of tan to get in.

11049.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
11049.description: When Squidward gets spritzed with plant growth spray, he becomes monstrously huge. // When Patrick realizes that he is the only one out of all his friends without a nose, he decides he needs to get a nose, too.

11050.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
11050.description: It's time to restock the secret Krabby Patty ingredient, and it is SpongeBob's duty to make sure the ingredient is delivered safely to the Krusty Krab. // Plankton has a customer who eats at the Chum Bucket every day.
